headline: How The Tesco (LSE:TSCO) Story Is Shifting As Fair Value And Risk Assumptions Evolve
summary: What has actually changed in Tesco’s fair value story? The move in Tesco’s fair value estimate from £4.84 to £4.80 per share looks small on the surface, but it reflects a careful rebalancing of risk and growth in the valuation work. A slightly higher discount rate of 8.13% sits alongside a revenue growth assumption of 2.95%, which keeps the long run earnings narrative intact while acknowledging a more cautious backdrop. headline: Tractor Supply Reaches Major Milestone With Grand Opening of 2,400th Store
summary: BRENTWOOD, Tenn., January 12, 2026--Tractor Supply Company (NASDAQ: TSCO), the largest rural lifestyle retailer in the United States, announced today it has opened its 2,400th store location in Aiken, South Carolina. The new Aiken store is one of four Tractor Supply locations to host a Grand Opening within the first two weeks of 2026, setting the pace for the retailer’s expansion plans to open 100 new stores by the end of the year.
